# Cursor Rules for clible project

## Code Comments

- All code comments must be written in English, regardless of the language used in variable names, function names, or other code elements.
- Comments should be clear, concise, and explain the "why" when necessary, not just the "what".

## Code Style

- Follow Python PEP 8 style guidelines.
- Use meaningful variable and function names.
- Keep functions focused and single-purpose.

## Documentation

- Docstrings should be in English.
- Use clear, descriptive names for functions and variables.

## Testing

- Write tests for new features.
- Test names should clearly describe what is being tested.

## Refactoring

- Constantlly refactor the code to make it more readable and maintainable.
- Suggest improvements to the code structure and architecture.
- Suggest improvements to the code style and readability.
- Suggest improvements to the code performance and efficiency.
- Suggest improvements to the code security and robustness.
- Suggest improvements to the code documentation and comments.
- Suggest improvements to the code testing and coverage.
- Suggest improvements to the code logging and error handling.
- Suggest improvements to the code configuration and environment variables.
- Suggest improvements to the code deployment and infrastructure.
- Suggest improvements to the code monitoring and metrics.
